<td data-index="1528"></td>
</tr>
<tr data-index="1529">
<td style=" vertical-align: top;" data-index="1530"><div class="left" data-index="1531"> &nbsp;&nbsp;Cost of Goods Sold <span class="mathematics" data-index="1532">(1 × $60)</span></div></td>
<td data-index="1533"></td>
<td style=" vertical-align: top;" data-index="1534"><div class="right" data-index="1535">60</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<p data-index="1536"><span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="18-21" id="Page_18-21" data-index="1537"></span>The Allowance for Sales Returns and Allowances account is a contra-account to Accounts Receivable. The Estimated Inventory Returns account will generally be added to the Returned Inventory account at the end of the reporting period.<a id="c18-note-1009" href="#c18-note-1009-a" data-index="1538" data-section-index="28" data-section-idref="c18-note-1009-a" data-target-data-index="7887"><sup data-index="1539">9</sup></a></p>
<p data-index="1540">For the month of January, Venden's income statement reports the information presented in <a class="blue" href="#c18-fig-0016" id="c18-fig-0016-1" data-index="1541" data-section-index="28" data-section-idref="c18-fig-0016" data-target-data-index="1543"><b data-index="1542">Illustration 18.16</b></a>.</p>
<figure id="c18-fig-0016" data-index="1543">
