<p data-index="1697">Venden records an accounts payable to Amaya to recognize that it owes Amaya for the return of two cameras. As indicated earlier, the Sales Returns and Allowances account is a contra-revenue account. The Returned Inventory account is used to separate returned inventory from regular inventory.</p>
<p data-index="1698">On January 31, 2020, Venden prepares financial statements. As indicated earlier, Venden estimates that the most likely outcome is that one more camera will be returned. Venden therefore makes the following adjusting entries.</p>
