<p data-index="5687">Outback Industries' net income for the quarter: <span class="mathematics" data-index="5688">$6,500,000 − $4,350,000 + $345,520 = $2,495,520</span>.</p></li>
<li data-index="5689"><b data-index="5690">b.</b> Whether a company will get paid for satisfying a performance obligation is not a consideration in determining revenue recognition. That is, the amount recognized is not adjusted for customer credit risk. If significant doubt exists at contract inception about collectibility, Outback reports the revenue gross and then presents an allowance for any impairment due to bad debts, which will reduce net income and which is reported as an operating expense in the income statement.</li>
</ul></li></ul>
</section>
